 on the role of cosmetic surgeons as gatekeepers and producers of desired appearances, Refashioning Race argues that cosmetic surgeons literally reshape race—both on patients' bodies and at the broader level of culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aRace. 0aSurgery, PlasticxHistoryy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520386730?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520386730423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520386730/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131926-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSLb2023  aZDB-23-UCY